This product takes naming and API-shape inspiration from nestjs-zod
(MIT, Copyright (c) Ben Lorantfy and contributors —
https://github.com/BenLorantfy/nestjs-zod), specifically:

- The `createZodDto` factory name and its class-with-static-schema shape.
- The `ZodValidationPipe` name and its role as a global validation pipe.
- The `ZodValidationException` name and its 400-response envelope.
- The `ZodSerializerInterceptor` name and its role as a response-validation
  interceptor.
- The `ZodSerializationException` name (the response-body shape differs in
  zod-nest — see docs/exceptions.md for the policy).
- The `ZodResponse` decorator name (the call shape differs: zod-nest's
  `ZodResponse` is stackable per status code and does not internally apply
  `@HttpCode`; see MIGRATION.md for the behavioural differences).

The implementation is a fresh rewrite for Zod v4 and OpenAPI 3.1, but the
familiar names lower the migration cost for projects coming from nestjs-zod
and acknowledge the prior art.

No code is lifted verbatim from nestjs-zod. If that changes in a future
release, the affected file(s) will carry the upstream MIT header.
